lastfm.summary: "'I Trawl the Megahertz' seems to be a portrait of a woman who is trying to make sense of her life by reviewing selected memories. She is like someone with their hand on a radio dial, turning into distant stations, listening to fragments of different broadcasts..." I Trawl the Megahertz, the 22-minute long title track of Paddy McAloon's 2003 solo debut (eventually reissued under the Prefab Sprout name in 2019), recounts fragmented memories of the narrators experiences in love and life atop swelling strings and circular motifs.
